article.description: 5 Davidson players in double figures in 76-57 victory
article.headline: 5 Davidson players in double figures in 76-57 victory
article.linkText: 5 Davidson players in double figures in 76-57 victory
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. -- Brian Sullivan scored 18 points and Jack Gibbs 17 to help Davidson pick up its fifth straight win with a 76-57 victory over Fordham on Saturday night. Tyler Kalinoski added 14 points, Oskar Michelsen 12 and Jordan Barham 10 for the Wildcats (19-6, 10-4 Atlantic 10), who shot 50 percent, including 11 of 26 3-point attempts. Bryan Smith scored 15 points to lead the Rams (8-7, 3-11) with Eric Paschall adding 14 and Nemanja Zarkovic 13. Fordham shot only 37.7 percent and turned the ball over 14 times to six miscues for Davidson. Davidson took the lead for good two minutes into the game and was up 38-25 by halftime. The lead would reach as many as 24 points in the second half. The victory left Davidson tied for second place with Dayton in the Atlantic 10, a game back of VCU and Rhode Island.
